## Methods (Brief)

This analysis ingests open-access scientific literature on {{ topic_title | default("the selected topic") }} from PubMed Central via NCBI E-utilities. Each paper is triaged at the abstract level (Claude Haiku 4.5). The deep set — ranked by sample size × design weight × extraction confidence **before** extraction — is fetched as full text from PMC Open Access (references stripped) and analysed by Claude Sonnet 4.6: factual extraction, then methodological appraisal with a **design-matched** risk-of-bias instrument, mechanistic phenotype mapping, and calibrated certainty. Every deep-extracted claim is grounded in a literal-quote provenance record, and each quote is verified to substring-match its source (quote-drift entries are pulled).

{% if (aggregates.rct_count | default(0)) == 0 %}
**Randomised controlled trials: 0.** This corpus contains no RCTs; intervention-efficacy questions are therefore **out of scope** for this run. This evidence map characterises observational signal and its certainty only.
{% else %}
**Randomised controlled trials: {{ aggregates.rct_count }}.**
{% endif %}

