## GRADE Certainty, by Outcome {{ "x" | calc }}

GRADE rates the certainty of a body of evidence **for a specific outcome** — never a single paper. Starting certainty is High if the body is RCT-dominated, Low if observational-dominated ([CALC]); each domain decision is a judgement ([LLM]); the arithmetic combining them is deterministic ([CALC]).

